Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It is interesting that no further information regarding the epidemiology of this outbreak and source of the _E. coli_ O157 has been reported. It is important to note that the teenager who was one of the 1st cases was involved before the petting zoo and was in contact with the hay for the hay maze. An incubation period of 1 day, if correct, suggests a large inoculum and suggests that the hay itself was grossly contaminated.

Whatcom County is in extreme northwestern Washington bordering British Columbia and can be found on a map at http://geology.com/county-map/washington-county-map.gif. - Mod.LL]

